**** African cultural transfer--pidginization and... 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ UP: <h-f...???>

Models of destruction, replication, or levelling of African cultures in their transit to the Americas generally fail to provide satisfactory explanations for the cultures actually encountered.  How can description of the process that took place (exemplified by the music) be approached?  Pidginization provides a key.  It may be in some ways considered as learning a second language or culture when that target is contested.

